CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1784387896
OL,3,CAndy Burnham promises to 'bring back
OL,4,Chope' as he becomes Labour Leader
OL,6,FAt a special conference in London,
OL,7,FShabana Mahmood, in her role as the
OL,8,Fchairperson of Labour's National
OL,9,FExecutive Committee, declared Burnham
OL,10,F"duly elected as leader of the Labour
OL,11,FParty" after joking that the
OL,12,Fcompetition was "hardly a nail biter".
OL,14,FBurnham was the only candidate to get
OL,15,Fthe required support to stand for
OL,16,Fparty leader as he was backed by 369
OL,17,Fof the party's 403 MPs, far surpassing
OL,18,Fthe 81 needed, and secured the support
OL,19,Fof eight of the 11 unions affiliated
OL,20,Fwith the party.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
